      <%= image_tag("administrator.jpg", class: "img-responsive img-rounded", alt: "Tired Administrator") %>
      <%= image_tag("divider-grey.png", class: "divider img-reponsive", alt: "Curved Divider") %>
      <h3><span class="text-primary">Teams move mountains ~ <span class="text-muted">The challenges facing our schools and communities are so complicated and multifaceted that it takes many eyes, minds, and hands to grapple with them.</span></h3 >
    </div>
    <div class="panel panel-default col-sm-9">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h3 class="panel-title">Administrator frustrations</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>Behavoir intervention data is incredibly difficult to aggregate, because it is often siloed off by teacher, and individual to every student.<span class = "text-primary">This hampers collaboration and effective teamwork.</span>. School leadership teams need better, more rhobust systems for gathering, interpreting, and acting on BIP data accross all gradelevels and teams.<p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <h4>Opacity - </h4>
            <p>One of the most consistent frustrations expressed by administrators is their inablity to quickly see an accurate picture of the effectiveness of interventions in place. School leaders need to be able to identify in real time the students, teachers, or teams that need more support. All school leaders recognize that the quicker this support becomes available the more effective it will be, but the turnaround time on current data management systems can mean weeks may go by before they are alerted to a problem.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h4>Documentation of services - </h4>
            <p>Accurately documenting the services a student with a BIP recieved is ultimately the responsiblity and liablity of the school. Having secure, redundant and persistant data storage, alongside a exhaustive report generation suite is crucial to a rhobust documentation of services for every student.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
